  "text": "Each branch in the proposed DASPP only includes 128 channels, where BN is also used for each branch to accelerate the network training. Moreover, considering the merits of shortcut [CITATION_1] , we also apply the shortcut to reuse the input feature maps of DASPP and facilitate the information flow. Since the padding operations are used, the output resolution of each branch is equal to the input one. All the feature maps are finally fused by using the simple element-wise addition.",
